The Federal Government yesterday reiterated that it will keep to its promise in lifting no fewer than 100 million Nigerians out of poverty, adding that the nation is on the part to food security and economic growth. The government, through the Permanent Secretary of Ministry of Science and Technology, Bitrus Bako Nabasu, stated this in Abuja while signing Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with Agro-Allied Green Technology Resource Centre Limited. He said, “We want to see that Nigerians are lifted out of poverty. We want to see that we help Mr President fulfil the promise he made at his inauguration in lifting 100 million Nigerians out of poverty in the next 10 years.” Speaking further on ravaging unemployment in the country, the Managing Director of Agro-Allied Green Technology Resource Centre Limited, Emeka Okengwu, disclosed that the introduction of technology into the Agro-allied sector by the Ministry of Science will create over 30m jobs. According to him, “The technology will not only reduce the stress associated with farming but will generate millions of jobs for both the country for the youths and the aged ones.” What the North East wants from Buhari Why we are organizing farmers’ summit – Arewa young farmers We want to commercialize research findings - FG